Polish Stocks: Bogdanka, Budimex, Lotos, Orlen, PZU Shares Move

-- B y   P a w e l   K o z l o w s k i   a n d   M a r e k   S t r z e l e c k i
-- 
2011-04-07T16:27:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-07/polish-stocks-bogdanka-budimex-lotos-orlen-pzu-shares-move.html
Poland ’s WIG20 Index closed with a
gain of 0.76, or 0.03 percent, to 2,928.95 at 5:30 p.m. in
Warsaw, the highest since May 28, 2008.  The following are among the most active stocks on the
 Warsaw Stock Exchange  today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Lubelski Wegiel Bogdanka SA (LWB)   gained 2.7 zloty, or
2.2 percent, to 126.6 zloty, the highest in more than two weeks.
Poland’s only publicly traded coal mine had its share-price
estimate increased 20 percent to 153 zloty at UniCredit SpA,
which cited rising coal prices. UniCredit kept its “buy”
recommendation for the stock.  Budimex SA (BDX)   snapped a four-day drop, jumping 7.7
zloty, or 7.6 percent, to 109.1 zloty, the highest close since
August 2007. The Polish building unit of Ferrovial SA aims for
2011 net income to be “at least close” to last year’s level of
267.4 million zloty ($96 million), Parkiet reported, citing
Chief Executive Officer Dariusz Blocher.  PKN Orlen SA (PKN PW), Poland’s biggest oil company, lost 1
zloty, or 1.7 percent, to 56.5 zloty.  Grupa Lotos SA (LTS)  ,
the second-largest refiner, declined 0.55 zloty, or 1.1 percent,
to 47.95 zloty. Brent crude oil fluctuated after a five-day
advance that took it to 31-month high yesterday.  PZU SA (PZU PW), Poland’s biggest insurer, advanced for a
sixth day, adding 2 zloty, or 0.5 percent, to 369 zloty, the
highest close since November. Goldman Sachs Group Inc. increased
its price estimate for the stock 5.9 percent to 392 zloty.  To contact the reporter on this story:
